National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan had a phone conversation with Emma Aparici, Chief Diplomatic Advisor to the President of Spain. Sullivan emphasized the Biden administration's dedication to enhancing the U.S.-Spain relationship and thanked Spain for hosting U.S. military forces. They agreed to collaborate on shared foreign policy concerns such as China, Latin America, and the Sahel. Additionally, they discussed the significance of working together on global challenges like the COVID-19 pandemic and climate change.